<p>Jan Mare≈° is a data scientist at <a href="https://vitad.io">Vitadio</a>, a health-care company which develops digital therapeutics for type 2 diabetes, and a research consultant at <a href="https://www.worldbank.org/en/home">The World Bank</a> for the Global Tax Incentives Database project. His former research in academia focused on economic growth, inequality, financial development, and tax evasion. Jan tought undergraduate classes of Macroeconomics <a href="https://is.cuni.cz/studium/predmety/index.php?id=94fdeac5d8c829836f77d9cc448e316f&amp;tid=&amp;do=predmet&amp;kod=JEB114" target="_blank">I</a>, <a href="https://is.cuni.cz/studium/predmety/index.php?id=94fdeac5d8c829836f77d9cc448e316f&amp;tid=&amp;do=predmet&amp;kod=JEB115" target="_blank">II</a>, and <a href="https://is.cuni.cz/studium/predmety/index.php?id=94fdeac5d8c829836f77d9cc448e316f&amp;tid=&amp;do=predmet&amp;kod=JEB102" target="_blank">Principles of Economics II</a>. He also has experience from public sector, where he worked in the economic modelling department at the Ministry of Finance of the Czech Republic.</p>

