<p>I am is a data scientist at Vitadio, a health-care company which develops digital therapeutics for type 2 diabetes, and a research consultant at The World Bank for the Global Tax Incentives Database project. My former research in academia focused on economic growth, inequality, financial development, and tax evasion. I tought undergraduate classes of Macroeconomics I, II, and Principles of Economics II. I also have experience from public sector, where I worked in the economic modelling department at the Ministry of Finance of the Czech Republic.</p>

